sentences: Bob Log III (born November 21, 1969) is an American slide guitar one-man band based in Tucson, Arizona, and Melbourne, Australia.
Log tours internationally, performing about 150 shows each year; he has made tours of North America, Europe, Japan and Australia, New Zealand, Mexico, Taiwan, and Iceland.
After six years of making music with Doo Rag, Bob began a solo career, warming up audiences bands, including R. L. Burnside, Blues Explosion, Ween, Franz Ferdinand, and Ani Difranco.
He began touring in North America, including performances in Toronto in 1999 and 2000.
Log credits years of drumming with his feet for his ability to simultaneously drum and support the weight of multiple people: "My legs are huge now.
